ndor the light does not turn on replace the units receiver logic board.";i:3;s:150:"It is not recommended to use a switch to power the garage door opener onoff as repetitive power cycling may damage the operators receiver logic board.";i:4;s:37:"I just recently purchased an 06 S500.";i:5;s:86:"I tried clear the codes for the garage door opener but the bottom light never flashes.";i:6;s:147:"Tried hitting the learn button on opener and then the programming button but still doesnt work and the light on the bottom of mirror never flashes.";i:7;s:159:"Garage door openers all have a switch known as a bypass switch that is used specifically for power outages or a motor not working or a dead garage door remote.";i:8;s:96:"The garage door opener should have a rope that has a handle attached to it normally this is red.";i:9;s:116:"This is a manual release handle that will disengage your garage doors trolley from where it is attached on the rail.";i:10;s:43:"When you pull on this rope the garage door.";i:11;s:140:"No light coming on when you push the button is leading me to believe you have a problem in the wiring harness or still possibly a bad board.";i:12;s:75:"You can purchase a power tester at local hardware store for a couple bucks.";i:13;s:116:"I would get one of these and make sure I still have power coming into the opener at the other end of the power cord.";i:14;s:56:"There is no green light or any other sign of it working.";i:15;s:48:"I tried pressing it a few times but no response.";i:16;s:67:"The opener still works with the remote outside the garage to enter.";i:17;s:117:"I opened the button and touched both wires together as mentioned in another post but that didnt open the garage door.";i:18;s:90:"Most newer garage door openers function by learning the frequency of the handheld openers.";i:19;s:194:"To reset the system you will need to locate the button on the motor that reads Learn or Home In many cases this button will be located on the same side as the devic